pr_body:
This pull request aims to solve the issue #870, updating the new widget protocol and implementing any new widgets

Things to do:
- [ ] Update sample notebooks
- [x] Implement the Link widgets
- [x] Implement jslink and jsdlink as helper functions
- [ ] Implement the Controller widget
- [x] Revise and improve documentation
- [x] Fix the OutputWidget

-- | Modifies a header and appends the version of the Widget Messaging Protocol as metadata
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 13, 43, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687726765, 'comment_body': "You can use `object` here like we do above, then we don't need to import `HashMap`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 13, 45, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687728168, 'comment_body': "I don't think we need these additional imports if we use `object`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 13, 47, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688092581, 'comment_body': 'This file was supposed to be ignored as is from IPython...

The widgets notebooks are on ihaskell-display/Examples', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 21, 20, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'daviddavo', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688101369, 'comment_body': 'The problem is that `Metadata` is `newtype Metadata = Metadata Object`, but the [`object`](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/aeson-1.5.6.0/docs/Data-Aeson.html#v:object) function returns a `Value`.

I saw that they use through the docs the `fromList` function to create an `Object`.

Another alternative could be extracting the `Object` with a lambda expression like `(\(Object o) -> o) $ object ["version .= pack v]`', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 21, 36, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'daviddavo', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688357344, 'comment_body': "Oh, good point, I didn't realise that. The way you currently do it is fine.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 13, 8, 57, 26, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688358089, 'comment_body': "I'll add a comment in case we forget about this later", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 13, 8, 58, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'daviddavo', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688395202, 'comment_body': 'These instructions are really nice.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 13, 9, 58, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'jamesdbrock', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688441843, 'comment_body': "Turns out we can't use `object`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 13, 11, 27, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688673594, 'comment_body': "Nit: I'd prefer if we removed this and used plain `fmap` or `<$>` instead.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 13, 17, 30, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 688928598, 'comment_body': 'Resolved!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 14, 13, 4, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vaibhavsagar', 'type': 'User'}]
